In a message dated 7/31/03 12:25:47 AM Central Daylight Time, 
airly2002@... writes:


> "Not yet, my sweet tigress"replied Hydras"I should wait a info for 
> Perceptor, If my feelingare true then I have to call to my old friend, Rodimus, after 
> that Blackstorm's life is in Rodimus' hand's... literally"
> 

She paused a moment. Watching him. Nodding but said nothing. The mention of 
Rodimus spurred her own wishes to discuss matters with him. 

Within her, she felt a burning, a sort of interesting... tingle. Up until 
now, she had forgotten about what Scourge had given her. 

Wincing & doubled over somewhat as it felt like a tiny piece of her was 
sucked out of her form.... out of her lasercore. "Unngh," trying not to make a 
sound.

--part1_1da.edfe7de.2c5a0597_boundary
